Supported by the Anglo American Group Foundation, Pro Mujer is an international, women’s development and microfinance NGO. Established in 1990 and focused on alleviating poverty across Latin America, Pro Mujer trailblazes new paths for low-income women in Latin America. The organisation aims to fuel leadership, empower women to transform their lives, and to ignite greater social and economic opportunities for families. This is achieved by providing access to financial services, education and training, and lifesaving health care. To learn more about Pro Mujer’s work and to join the community, click here. More from the Anglo American partner zone:Copy on this page is paid for and provided by Anglo American, sponsor of the social impact hub